708658f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue, east side, north from East 39th to 41st Street's, showing prominently the Union League Club. This is located at the N.E. corner of 39th Street and is a magnificent specimen of Queene Anne architecture. The F.W. Woolworth Co. had a modern store structure erected on this site in 1938. Ths Club had previously moved to their modern Colonial building at the S.W. corner of Park
Avenue and East 37th Street.
About 1890
Gift Thru New York Historical Society
May be reproduced
